peter blank presentation at arlis sulair sulair home searchworks e journals databases off campus access ask us sulair news logo sulair news home all articles submit article search sulair news library web sites searchworks databases az socrates google books google scholar search this site sulair news about sulair news back issues get email announcements submit article user login login with your sunet id home groups sulair news peter blank presentation at arlis peter blank recently gave a paper at the 2010 art libraries society of north america annual conference in boston animating the archive playing in the fields of cultural production case study 1959 more than robert frank's the americans the paper reconceptualizes traditional notions of archive as a first step towards the development of innovative collections and instructional practices using the writings of ts eliot thomas kuhn and pierre bourdieu to create a methodological framework for a cultural examination of american photography in the late 1950s the project will result in an exhibition and web site surrounding frank's the americans at the art & architecture library in fall 2010 peter's presentation was paired with michael mittleman's associate director center for advanced visual studies mit who spoke on the mit future archive project designed to publish contemporary artists archives immediately online within hours of actual processes and collaborations well done peter chris bourg assistant university librarian for public services submitted by mchris stanford edu on tue 05 11 2010 16 24 back stanford university stanford california 94305 650 725 1064 terms of use copyright complaints
